    ‚àá {r}‚Üê_Register(method path rarg);handler;options;norm;existing
      :Access Private Instance
      :If 1‚âÝ‚â°rarg                           ‚çù nested: ('HandlerName' options)
          (handler options)‚Üêrarg
      :ElseIf ‚çï‚çõ‚â°rarg
          handler‚Üêrarg                     ‚çù simple string
          options‚Üê()
      :Else
        ‚éïSIGNAL ‚äÇ('EN' 11)('Message' ('STARK: Right argument to Register must be a string (handler name) or a 2-element vector (handler name, options)'))
      :EndIf
      ‚çù Check for duplicate routes: normalize {param} segments so {id} and {user_id} match
      norm‚Üê_NormalizePath path
      :If 0<‚â¢_routes
          existing‚Üê(_routes[;1]‚àä‚ç•‚éïC ‚äÇmethod)‚åø_routes
          :If 0<‚â¢existing
              :If (‚äÇnorm)‚àä_NormalizePath¬®existing[;2]
                  ‚éïSIGNAL ‚äÇ('EN' 11)('Message' ('STARK: Duplicate route: ',method,' ',path,' conflicts with an existing registration'))
              :EndIf
          :EndIf
      :EndIf
      r‚Üê(
        method
        ,path
        handler
        options
      )
      _routes‚ç™‚Üêr
    ‚àá

    ‚àá r‚ÜêRegister routes
      :Access Public
      ‚çù Matrix mode:   N√ó4 matrix of (method path handler spec)
      ‚çù Namespace mode: vector of namespaces, each with .method .path .handler and optionally .spec
      :If 2=‚ç¥‚ç¥routes
        :If _routes[;2]{0‚â¢‚â¢‚äÉ‚à©/{_NormalizePath¬®‚çµ}¬®‚ç∫ ‚çµ}routes[;2]
            ‚éïSIGNAL ‚äÇ('EN' 11)('Message' ('STARK: Duplicate routes detected'))
        :EndIf
        routes[;2]‚Üê,¬®routes[;2]
        _routes‚ç™‚Üê4‚Üë[2]routes,()
      :Else
        :For ns :In ,routes
          :If 9=ns.‚éïNC'spec'
              _Register ns.method ns.path (ns.handler ns.spec)
          :Else
              _Register ns.method ns.path ns.handler
          :EndIf
        :EndFor
      :EndIf
      r‚Üê_routes
    ‚àá

    ‚çù Cover function for 7162‚å∂ (mangle string into valid APL name)
    _Mangle‚Üê{0(7162‚å∂)‚çµ}

    ‚çù Replace {param} segments with a placeholder so structurally identical paths match
    _NormalizePath‚Üê{‚çµ/‚ç®~+\‚àä+/¬Ø1 0‚åΩ¬®1 ¬Ø1√ó‚Üì'{}'‚àò.=‚çµ}

    ‚àá r‚Üê{value}DebugLevel level
    ‚çù monadic: return 1 if level is within Debug (powers of 2)
    ‚çù dyadic:  return value unless level is within Debug
      r‚Üê‚à®/((7‚ç¥2)‚ä§‚äÉDebug)‚à®.‚àß(7‚ç¥2)‚ä§level
      :If 0‚âÝ‚éïNC'value'
          r‚Üêvalue/‚ç®~r
      :EndIf
    ‚àá

    stopIf‚Üê{1‚àä‚çµ:-‚éïTRAP‚Üê0 'C' '‚éï‚Üê''Stopped for debugging... (Press Ctrl-Enter)''' ‚ãÑ shy‚Üê0}

    ‚çù pattern pathMatch path ‚Üí (matched pathParams)
    pathMatch‚Üê{
        patSplit pathSplit‚Üê'/'(‚âÝ‚äÜ‚ä¢)¬®‚ç∫ ‚çµ
        pathSplit‚â¢‚ç•‚â¢patSplit:0()
        varMask‚Üê'{'=‚äÉ¬®patSplit
        ‚â¢/(‚äÇ~varMask)/¬®patSplit pathSplit:0()
        names‚Üê({1‚Üì¬Ø1‚Üì‚çµ}¬®patSplit[‚ç∏varMask])
        1(()‚éïVSET‚Üì‚çâ‚Üënames(pathSplit[‚ç∏varMask]))
    }

    ‚çù Route an incoming Jarvis request to the matching handler
    ‚àá result‚Üê_Dispatch req;routes;r;matched;pp;m;err
      :Access Public Instance
      stopIf DebugLevel 64                          ‚çù stop before routing
      routes‚Üê(_routes[;1] ‚àä‚ç•‚éïC ‚äÇreq.Method)‚åø_routes
      :If 0=‚â¢routes
          req.Fail 404
          result‚Üê(
            detail: 'Not Found'
          )
          :Return
      :EndIf
      m pp‚Üê{(‚äÉ‚çµ) (‚çµ‚äÉ‚çõ/2‚äÉ‚çµ)}‚Üì‚çâ‚Üëroutes[;2] pathMatch¬®‚äÇreq.Endpoint
      r‚Üêm‚åøroutes
      :If 1‚âÝ‚â¢pp
          req.Fail 404
          result‚Üê(
            detail: 'Not Found'
          )
          :Return
      :EndIf
      r‚Üêr[1;]
      req.PathParams‚Üê‚äÉpp ‚çù Shouldn't have multiple matches.
      req.QueryParams‚Üê() ‚éïVSET ‚Üìreq.QueryParams
      :If '_'=‚äÉ3‚äÉr
          result‚Üê(‚çé3‚äÉr)req          ‚çù internal handler (on Stark)
      :Else
          :If DebugLevel 32
              ‚éï‚Üê'STARK: ',req.Method,' ',req.Endpoint,' ‚Üí ',3‚äÉr
          :EndIf
          stopIf DebugLevel 2              ‚çù stop before user handler
          :Trap 0 DebugLevel 1             ‚çù disable trap if bit 1 set (stop on error)
              result‚Üê(Handlers‚çé3‚äÉr)req
          :Else
              :If ~0‚àä‚ç¥OnErrorFn
                  err‚Üê()‚éïNS ‚éïDMX          ‚çù deep clone ‚éïDMX before req.Fail may alter it
                  req.Fail 500
                  result‚Üêerr(Handlers‚çéOnErrorFn)req
              :Else
                  ‚éïSIGNAL‚äÇ‚éïDMX.(('EN'EN)('EM'EM)('Message'(OSError{‚çµ,2‚åΩ(√ó‚â¢‚äÉ‚ç¨‚ç¥2‚åΩ‚ç∫,‚äÇ'')/'") ("',‚äÉ‚ç¨‚ç¥2‚åΩ‚ç∫}Message))) ‚çù RESIGNAL
              :EndIf
          :EndTrap
      :EndIf
